rification\\n\\n```bash\\nmise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci\\n```\\n\\nAfter deploying: run `entire enable --force` in the test repo to regenerate the hook files, then verify the IDE hooks fire by chatting in the Kiro IDE.\\n\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"f600644a-0d2c-438f-8b50-1ba0638b425a\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/wt/kiro-oneshot\",\"sessionId\":\"4ab3ddd7-2bb2-4d33-bbe6-7ee25ce1f55e\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/kiro-oneshot\",\"slug\":\"glittery-waddling-parrot\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01WbC5YheiMQFTnM1L8pgSPs\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"\\n\\n`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`\\nThis is a classic \\\"silent failure\\\" bug — the Kiro IDE simply ignores hooks with an unrecognized `then.type` value without any error logging. The fix is a one-word change (`\\\"command\\\"` → `\\\"runCommand\\\"`), but it's the kind of bug that can take hours to diagnose because there's no feedback from the IDE when the type is wrong.\\n`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`\\n\\nLet me read the three files that need changes.\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":22907,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":31684,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":22907},\"output_tokens\":2,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYgms3hTyWcqx4Ga8Mx7S\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"4224ad5a-fe88-4e2f-8f06-eacac88db666\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-03T20:25:47.147Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"4224ad5a-fe88-4e2f-8f06-eacac88db666\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/wt/kiro-oneshot\",\"sessionId\":\"4ab3ddd7-2bb2-4d33-bbe6-7ee25ce1f55e\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/kiro-oneshot\",\"sl