Users/alisha/Projects/wt/kiro-oneshot\",\"sessionId\":\"4ab3ddd7-2bb2-4d33-bbe6-7ee25ce1f55e\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/kiro-oneshot\",\"slug\":\"glittery-waddling-parrot\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01CyYvJS8of64mKJ2d9ZBiZ1\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→# Kiro Agent Integration\\n     2→\\n     3→Implementation one-pager for the Kiro (Amazon AI coding CLI) agent integration.\\n     4→\\n     5→## Identity\\n     6→\\n     7→| Field | Value |\\n     8→|-------|-------|\\n     9→| Package | `kiro` |\\n    10→| Registry Key | `kiro` |\\n    11→| Agent Type | `Kiro` |\\n    12→| Binary | `kiro-cli` |\\n    13→| Preview | Yes |\\n    14→| Protected Dir | `.kiro` |\\n    15→\\n    16→## Hook Events (5 CLI + 4 IDE)\\n    17→\\n    18→| Kiro Hook (camelCase) | CLI Subcommand (kebab-case) | EventType | Notes |\\n    19→|----------------------|----------------------------|-----------|-------|\\n    20→| `agentSpawn` | `agent-spawn` | `SessionStart` | Agent initializes |\\n    21→| `userPromptSubmit` | `user-prompt-submit` | `TurnStart` | stdin includes `prompt` field |\\n    22→| `preToolUse` | `pre-tool-use` | `nil, nil` | Pass-through |\\n    23→| `postToolUse` | `post-tool-use` | `nil, nil` | Pass-through |\\n    24→| `stop` | `stop` | `TurnEnd` | Checkpoint trigger |\\n    25→\\n    26→No `SessionEnd` hook exists — sessions end implicitly (similar to Cursor).\\n    27→\\n    28→## Hook Configuration\\n    29→\\n    30→### CLI Agent Hooks\\n    31→\\n    32→**File:** `.kiro/agents/entire.json`\\n    33→\\n    34→We own the entire file — no round-trip preservation needed (unlike Cursor's shared `hooks.json`).\\n    35→\\n    36→**Format:**\\n    37→```json\\n    38→{\\n    39→  \\\"name\\\": \\\"entire\\\",\\n    40→  \\\"tools\\\": [\\\"read\\\", \\\"write\\\", \\\"shell\\\", \\\"grep\\\", \\\"glob\\\", \\\"aws\\\", \\\"report\\\",\\n    41→            \\\"introspect\\\", \\\"knowledge\\\", \\\"thinking\\\", \\\"todo\\\", \\\"delegate\\\"],\\n    42→  \\\"hooks\\\": {\\n    43→    \\\"agentSpawn\\\": [{\\\"command\\\": \\\"entire hooks kiro agent-spawn\\\"}],\\n    44→    \\\"userPromptSubmit\\\": [{\\\"command\\\": \\\"entire hooks kiro user-prompt-submit\\\"}],\\n    45→    \\\"preToolUse\\\": [{\\\"command\\\": \\\"entire hooks kiro pre-tool-use\\\"}],\\n    46→    \\\"postToolUse\\\": [{\\\"command\\\": \\\"entire hooks kiro post-tool-use\\\"}],\\n    47→    \\\"stop\\\": [{\\\"command\\\": \\\"entire hooks kiro stop\\\"}]\\n    48→  }\\n    49→}\\n    50→```\\n    51→\\n    52→Note: The file is a Kiro agent definition. Hooks must be nested under the `hooks` field.\\n    53→Required top-level fields: `name`. Optional: `$schema`, `description`, `prompt`, `mcpServers`,\\n    54→`tools`, `toolAliases`, `allowedTools`, `resources`, `hooks`, `toolsSettings`, `model`, etc.\\n    55→\\n    56→**Important:** The `tools` array must include all default Kiro tools. Without it, `--agent entire`\\n    57→restricts the model to zero tools. The tool names come from `~/.kiro/agents/agent_config.json.example`.\\n    58→\\n    59→### IDE Hook Configuration\\n    60→\\n    61→**Directory:** `.kiro/hooks/`\\n    62→\\n    63→The Kiro IDE (VS Code extension) reads hooks from individual `.kiro/hooks/*.kiro.hook` files.\\n    64→Unlike CLI hooks (nested in `entire.json`), each IDE hook is a standalone JSON file.\\n    65→\\n    66→**IDE hook files installed (4 total):**\\n    67→\\n    68→| File | `when.type` | Command |\\n    69→|------|-------------|---------|\\n    70→| `entire-prompt-submit.kiro.hook` | `promptSubmit` | `entire hooks kiro user-prompt-submit` |\\n    71→| `entire-stop.kiro.hook` | `agentStop` | `entire hooks kiro stop` |\\n    72→| `entire-pre-tool-use.kiro.hook` | `preToolUse` | `entire hooks kiro pre-tool-use` |\\n    73→| `entire-post-tool-use.kiro.hook` | `postToolUse` | `entire hooks kiro post-tool-use` |\\n    74→\\n    75→No `agentSpawn` IDE hook — the IDE has no such trigger. The first `promptSubmit` serves as session start.\\n    76→\\n    77→**Format:**\\n    78→```json\\n    79→{\\n    80→  \\\"enabled\\\": true,\\n    81→  \\\"name\\\": \\\"entire-prompt-submit\\\",\\n    82→  \\\"description\\\": \\\"Entire CLI promptSubmit hook\\\",\\n    83→  \\\"version\\\": \\\"1\\\",\\n    84→  \\\"when\\\": {\\n    85→    \\\"type\\\": \\\"promptSubmit\\\"\\n    86→  },\\n    87→  \\\"then\\\": {\\n    88→    \\\"type\\\": \\\"runCommand\\\",\\n    89→    \\\"command\\\": \\\"entire hooks kiro user-prompt-submit\\\"\\n    90→  }\\n    91→}\\n    92→```\\n    93→\\n    94→**Key difference from CLI hooks:** IDE hooks deliver data via environment variables (e.g.,\\n    95→`USER_PROMPT` for the user's prompt) rather than JSON on stdin. The lifecycle parsers handle\\n    96→empty stdin gracefully by reading from environment variables as a fallback.\\n    97→\\n    98→## Agent Activation\\n    99→\\n   100→Hooks only fire when `--agent entire` is passed to `kiro-cli chat`. Without this flag,\\n   101→`.kiro/agents/entire.json` is not loaded and hooks do not execute.\\n   102→\\n   103→IDE hooks in `.kiro/hooks/` are loaded automatically by the Kiro IDE without requiring\\n   104→an explicit agent flag.\\n   105→\\n   106→**`--no-interactive` mode:** Does not fire agent hooks. All E2E tests use interactive (tmux) mode.\\n   107→\\n   108→**TUI prompt indicator:** `!>` in trust-all mode (with `-a` flag). The `Credits:` line\\n   109→appears after each agent response and serves as a reliable completion marker.\\n   110→\\n   111→## Hook Data Delivery\\n   112→\\n   113→### CLI Mode (stdin JSON)\\n   114→\\n   115→CLI hooks (`kiro-cli chat --agent entire`) receive a JSON structure on stdin:\\n   116→```json\\n   117→{\\n   118→  \\\"hook_event_name\\\": \\\"userPromptSubmit\\\",\\n   119→  \\\"cwd\\\": \\\"/path/to/repo\\\",\\n   120→  \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"user message\\\",\\n   121→  \\\"tool_name\\\": \\\"fs_write\\\",\\n   122→  \\\"tool_input\\\": \\\"...\\\",\\n   123→  \\\"tool_response\\\": \\\"...\\\"\\n   124→}\\n   125→```\\n   126→\\n   127→Fields are populated based on the hook event — `prompt` only for `userPromptSubmit`, tool fields only for tool hooks.\\n   128→\\n   129→### IDE Mode (environment variables)\\n   130→\\n   131→IDE hooks (`.kiro/hooks/*.kiro.hook`) receive **no stdin**. Data is delivered via environment variables:\\n   132→- `USER_PROMPT` — the user's prompt text (for `promptSubmit` hooks)\\n   133→\\n   134→The lifecycle parsers handle empty stdin gracefully: if stdin is empty, they fall back to reading\\n   135→environment variables for prompt data and use `paths.WorktreeRoot()` for CWD.\\n   136→\\n   137→## Transcript Storage\\n   138→\\n   139→**Source:** SQLite database at `~/Library/Application Support/kiro-cli/data.sqlite3` (macOS)\\n   140→or `~/.local/share/kiro-cli/data.sqlite3` (Linux).\\n   141→\\n   142→**Table:** `conversations_v2`\\n   143→- `key` column: CWD path (used for lookup)\\n   144→- `value` column: JSON blob with conversation data\\n   145→- `updated_at` column: timestamp for ordering\\n   146→\\n   147→**Conversation JSON structure:**\\n   148→```json\\n   149→{\\n   150→  \\\"conversation_id\\\": \\\"uuid-v4\\\",\\n   151→  \\\"history\\\": [\\n   152→    {\\\"role\\\": \\\"user\\\", \\\"content\\\": [{\\\"type\\\": \\\"text\\\", \\\"text\\\": \\\"...\\\"}]},\\n   153→    {\\\"role\\\": \\\"assistant\\\", \\\"content\\\": [{\\\"type\\\": \\\"text\\\", \\\"text\\\": \\\"...\\\"}, {\\\"type\\\": \\\"tool_use\\\", \\\"name\\\": \\\"fs_write\\\", \\\"input\\\": {...}}]},\\n   154→    {\\\"role\\\": \\\"request_metadata\\\", \\\"input_tokens\\\": 150, \\\"output_tokens\\\": 80}\\n   155→  ]\\n   156→}\\n   157→```\\n   158→\\n   159→## Session ID Discovery\\n   160→\\n   161→Hook stdin does not include session ID. We query SQLite by CWD:\\n   162→```sql\\n   163→SELECT json_extract(value, '$.conversation_id')\\n   164→FROM conversations_v2\\n   165→WHERE key = '<cwd>'\\n   166→ORDER BY updated_at DESC LIMIT 1\\n   167→```\\n   168→\\n   169→## SQLite Access Strategy\\n   170→\\n   171→Uses `sqlite3` CLI (pre-installed on macOS/Linux) rather than a Go library to avoid CGO dependencies. Same approach as OpenCode's `opencode export` CLI.\\n   172→\\n   173→**Test mock:** `ENTIRE_TEST_KIRO_MOCK_DB=1` env var causes the agent to skip SQLite queries and use pre-written mock files.\\n   174→\\n   175→## File Modification Tools\\n   176→\\n   177→Tools that modify files on disk:\\n   178→- `fs_write` — write file content\\n   179→- `str_replace` — string replacement in files\\n   180→- `create_file` — create new files\\n   181→- `write_file` — write/overwrite files\\n   182→- `edit_file` — edit existing files\\n   183→\\n   184→## Caching\\n   185→\\n   186→Transcript data is cached to `.entire/tmp/<sessionID>.json` (same pattern as OpenCode).\\n   187→\"}]},\"uuid\":\"a84d1a7f-5dd9-4125-95aa-e5a6daa25c1e\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-03T20:37:00.825Z\"},\"normalizedMessages\":[],\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"ad49515a0b5c8ee00\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_011prmDnVySwAKy2osYDRHWC\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01NqxdpBNvCjkkUjBRJfsfto\",\"uuid\":\"d685d537-d875-4de1-8698-c9c809f3bb24\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-03T20:37:01.228Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"d685d537-d875-4de1-8698-c9c809f3bb24\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/wt/kiro-oneshot\",\"sessionId\":\"4ab3ddd7-2bb2-4d33-bbe6-7ee25ce1f55e\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/kiro-oneshot\",\"slug\":\"glittery-waddling-parrot\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-03T20:37:01.380Z\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_01R2THb2KMtdRD5gMh5RGLXj\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"