submit\\\",\\n  \\\"description\\\": \\\"Entire CLI promptSubmit hook\\\",\\n  \\\"version\\\": \\\"1\\\",\\n  \\\"when\\\": {\\n    \\\"type\\\": \\\"promptSubmit\\\"\\n  },\\n  \\\"then\\\": {\\n    \\\"type\\\": \\\"runCommand\\\",\\n    \\\"command\\\": \\\"entire hooks kiro user-prompt-submit\\\"\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n## Key Findings on Auto-Approval\\n\\n**Important:** I found **NO support for auto-approval or trust settings in the `kiroIDEHookThen` struct**. The struct only has two fields:\\n- `Type` — currently only supports `\\\"runCommand\\\"` (not documented for other types)\\n- `Command` — the shell command to execute\\n\\n**No fields exist for:**\\n- `autoApprove`, `auto_approve`, `approve`, `approveAutomatically`\\n- `requireApproval`, `promptToApprove`, `requiresConfirmation`\\n- `trust`, `trustMode`, `alwaysApprove`\\n\\n## Kiro IDE Trust-All Mode\\n\\nThe E2E tests reference **`-a` flag (trust-all mode)** in the kiro-cli command:\\n```go\\nargs := []string{\\\"chat\\\", \\\"-a\\\", \\\"--agent\\\", \\\"entire\\\"}  // -a = trust-all mode\\n```\\n\\nThe `-a` flag is passed to `kiro-cli` itself, not configured in hook files. The `!>` prompt indicator appears when running with `-a` (trust-all mode).\\n\\n## Implications\\n\\nTo enable hooks to run **without user confirmation** in Kiro, you would need to:\\n1. **Use the `-a` flag** when invoking `kiro-cli chat` (passed at the CLI level, not in hook files)\\n2. **Hooks themselves cannot control auto-approval** — the hook file format has no fields for this\\n\\nThe hook system in `.kiro/hooks/*.kiro.hook` files is purely for **triggering commands at specific events** (promptSubmit, agentStop, preToolUse, postToolUse). Approval/confirmation is handled at the kiro-cli application level via command-line flags, not hook file configuration.\\n\\n## File Paths for Reference\\n\\n- **Hook struct definitions:** `/Users/alisha/Projects/wt/kiro-oneshot/cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/types.go` (lines 37-59)\\n- **Hook ins