ngs\\n- Check for existing configurations first\\n- Prompt users before modifying workspace settings\\n\\nThe issue remains open and is marked as pending a maintainer response from the Kiro team.\"}]},\"uuid\":\"b1cfa7bb-ecae-4446-a35c-ff3f9706781d\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-03T21:24:12.840Z\",\"toolUseResult\":{\"bytes\":275489,\"code\":200,\"codeText\":\"OK\",\"result\":\"# Kiro's Automatic .vscode/settings.json Configuration\\n\\nBased on the issue report, Kiro automatically creates a `.vscode/settings.json` file containing:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\\"kiroAgent.configureMCP\\\": \\\"Disabled\\\"}\\n```\\n\\n## Key Points\\n\\nThe document does not mention `kiroAgent.trustedCommands` or provide information about its format. The only setting explicitly documented in this issue is the MCP configuration flag that Kiro creates during autofix operations.\\n\\n## The Problem\\n\\nAccording to the report, this automatic file creation causes conflicts when team members use different development environments. The issue states that Kiro creates this setting \\\"during an autofix operation, which conflicts with existing MCP configurations\\\" that VS Code developers might be using.\\n\\nThe reporter suggests Kiro should either:\\n- Avoid creating conflicting settings\\n- Check for existing configurations first\\n- Prompt users before modifying workspace settings\\n\\nThe issue remains open and is marked as pending a maintainer response from the Kiro team.\",\"durationMs\":4181,\"url\":\"https://github.com/kirodotdev/Kiro/issues/3628\"},\"sourceToolAssistantUUID\":\"6e887245-ffdb-4549-b2ef-a06e01afe759\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"b1cfa7bb-ecae-4446-a35c-ff3f9706781d\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/wt/kiro-oneshot\",\"sessionId\":\"4ab3ddd7-2bb2-4d33-bbe6-7ee25ce1f55e\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/kiro-oneshot\",\"slug\":\"glittery-waddling-parrot\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01CoT5xxTN6H5UWZb3ekmbuL\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"thinking\",\"thinking\":\"So the Kiro IDE uses `.vscode/settings.json` for workspace-level settings, and `kiroAgent.trustedCommands` is a VS Code/Kiro IDE setting. To auto-approve our hook commands, we need to add `entire hooks kiro *` (or `entire *`) to this setting when running `entire enable`.\\n\\nBut wait — there's also the local dev mode where commands start with `go run ${KIRO_PROJECT_DIR}/cmd/entire/main.go hooks kiro ...`. We'd need to handle that too.\\n\\nLet me think about the approach:\\n\\n1. During `InstallHooks`, after installing the hook files, we should also ensure `.vscode/settings.json` has `kiroAgent.trustedCommands` configured with the appropriate command prefix.\\n\\n\\n2. When merging these settings, I need to preserve any existing configuration rather than overwriting it.\\n\\nThe user wants this to happen automatically when they run `entire enable`, so the implementation should handle updating `.vscode/settings.json` with the trusted command patterns while being careful not to lose other settings that might already be there.\\n\\nFor the actual patterns, I'm thinking `\\\"entire hooks *\\\"` for production and the full path version for local development. But this also means I need to handle reading and merging JSON properly, deal with the file potentially not existing, handle uninstall scenarios, and write tests for all these cases. Let me work through the plan for this.\",\"signature\":\"\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":1218,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":88511,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":1218},\"output_tokens\":8,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYgrKupRGx4hn4Ki7yeyt\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"fd9b6cfb-98d0-4827-8a52-0e3028cdbd71\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-03T21:24:26.47