ent.trustedCommands vscode settings.json trusted commands 2025 2026\\\"\\n\\nLinks: [{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Terminal integration - IDE - Docs - Kiro\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://kiro.dev/docs/chat/terminal/\\\"},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"GitHub - ghuntley/amazon-kiro.kiro-agent-source-code-analysis\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://github.com/ghuntley/amazon-kiro.kiro-agent-source-code-analysis\\\"},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Kiro IDE Review: Spec-Driven AI Agent Development vs Traditional Coding Assistants – Lothar Schulz\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://www.lotharschulz.info/2025/07/20/kiro-ide-review-spec-driven-ai-agent-development-vs-traditional-coding-assistants/\\\"},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Kiro IDE automatically creates settings.json in .vscode folder · Issue #3628 · kirodotdev/Kiro\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://github.com/kirodotdev/Kiro/issues/3628\\\"},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"AWS Kiro: Arbitrary Code Execution via Indirect Prompt Injection · Embrace The Red\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://embracethered.com/blog/posts/2025/aws-kiro-aribtrary-command-execution-with-indirect-prompt-injection/\\\"},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"CLI commands - CLI - Docs - Kiro\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://kiro.dev/docs/cli/reference/cli-commands/\\\"},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Need persistent trusted command settings for default kiro agent · Issue #4384 · kirodotdev/Kiro\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://github.com/kirodotdev/Kiro/issues/4384\\\"},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Migrating from VSCode - IDE - Docs - Kiro\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://kiro.dev/docs/guides/migrating-from-vscode/\\\"},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Trusted Command List Not Registering · Issue #22 · kirodotdev/Kiro\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://github.com/kirodotdev/Kiro/issues/22\\\"},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Kiro for Claude Code - Visual Studio Marketplace\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=heisebaiyun.kiro-for-cc\\\"}]\\n\\nBased on the search results, I found comprehensive information about the Kiro IDE's `kiroAgent.trustedCommands` setting in VS Code's `settings.json` file.\\n\\n## Overview\\n\\nKiro trusted commands use prefix matching to automatically approve commands that start with specific patterns.\\n\\n## Configuration\\n\\nYou can configure trusted commands in Settings → Kiro Agent: Trusted Commands at both the user level (global across all workspaces) and workspace level (specific to your current project). The settings can be added directly to `.vscode/settings.json`.\\n\\n## Examples\\n\\nFor example with configuration: `{ \\\"kiroAgent.trustedCommands\\\": [\\\"npm *\\\", \\\"git *\\\"], \\\"kiroAgent.commandDenylist\\\": [\\\"--force\\\", \\\"sudo\\\"] }`\\n\\nConfiguration example at workspace level: `{ \\\"kiroAgent.trustedCommands\\\": [ \\\"npm run test:run *\\\", \\\"npm run security: *\\\", \\\"npm test *\\\" ] }`\\n\\n## How Matching Works\\n\\nKiro trusted commands uses string prefix matching to determine if a command should be automatically trusted. Uses * to trust any command string that starts with the specified prefix. The trust system only checks the beginning of the command string - if it matches, the entire command is trusted, including any chained commands, pipes, or redirects.\\n\\n## Important Security Considerations\\n\\nThe trust system puts responsibility on you to carefully configure trusted command patterns. Commands with potentially dangerous operations (like rm -rf) will be accepted if they match your trusted patterns and are not in the denylist.\\n\\n\\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks.\"}]},\"uuid\":\"10831224-45da-41ef-896c-b7df48546ae3\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-03T21:27:15.113Z\"},\"normalizedMessages\":[],\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"a3065ba1879174194\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01BaQ1832M6d2CsCXHWx2VQm\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01CsWwmqfd9QsiE1zMaUHxqk\",\"uuid\":\"49087219-7d26-4b93-a54c-db714dcc7ab1\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-03T21:27:15.114Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"49087219-7d26-4