y return still triggers correctly.\\n\\n2. **Test isolation**: Tests that use `t.Chdir` cannot be parallelized. The existing hook tests already follow this pattern (no `t.Parallel()` calls), so the new tests fit naturally.\\n\\n3. **File permissions**: `.vscode/settings.json` is written with `0o600` (matching the pattern for `.kiro/agents/entire.json`). The `.vscode/` directory is created with `0o750`.\\n\\n4. **Race between install steps**: If `installIDEHooks` succeeds but `installTrustedCommands` fails, the hooks exist but are not trusted. This is acceptable because a subsequent `entire enable` will detect the missing trusted commands (via the idempotency check) and retry.\\n\\n5. **`.vscode/` in `.gitignore`**: Some projects exclude `.vscode/` from version control. This is fine -- the trusted commands are workspace-level configuration and should be set per-developer anyway, similar to other VS Code workspace settings. If the project does commit `.vscode/settings.json`, our pattern will appear in the diff, which is actually desirable for team onboarding.\\n\\n### Critical Files for Implementation\\n\\n- `/Users/alisha/Projects/wt/kiro-oneshot/cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/hooks.go` - Core file to modify: add `installTrustedCommands`, `uninstallTrustedCommands`, `trustedCommandsPresent`, and integrate into `InstallHooks`/`UninstallHooks`\\n- `/Users/alisha/Projects/wt/kiro-oneshot/cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/hooks_test.go` - Add all test cases for the new trusted commands functionality\\n- `/Users/alisha/Projects/wt/kiro-oneshot/cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/AGENT.md` - Document the trusted commands configuration\\n- `/Users/alisha/Projects/wt/kiro-oneshot/cmd/entire/cli/agent/claudecode/hooks.go` - Reference pattern for `map[string]json.RawMessage` round-trip JSON editing\\n- `/Users/alisha/Projects/wt/kiro-oneshot/cmd/entire/cli/jsonutil/json.go` - `MarshalIndentWithNewline` utility used for consistent JSON formatting\"},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"agentId: a3065ba18791