tUninstallHooks_PreservesOtherTrustedCommands` — only our patterns removed\\n- `TestUninstallHooks_RemovesBothProdAndLocalDevPatterns` — cleans up both modes\\n- `TestUninstallHooks_RemovesKeyWhenEmpty` — key deleted when array becomes empty\\n- `TestTrustedCommandPattern` — unit test for pattern helper (parallel)\\n- `TestTrustedCommandsPresent` — table-driven unit test (parallel)\\n- `TestInstallTrustedCommands_InvalidJSON` — error handling\\n\\n### 3. `cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/AGENT.md` — Document the feature\\n\\nAdd \\\"Trusted Commands Configuration\\\" section after \\\"IDE Hook Configuration\\\" documenting the `.vscode/settings.json` management.\\n\\n## Key Design Decisions\\n\\n- **Pattern**: `\\\"entire hooks kiro *\\\"` (narrow, least privilege) rather than `\\\"entire *\\\"` (too broad)\\n- **No count change**: Trusted commands are supporting config, not hooks — `InstallHooks` still returns 9\\n- **Uninstall removes both modes**: `trustedCommandPatterns()` returns both prod and local dev patterns so switching modes doesn't leave stale entries\\n- **Never delete `.vscode/settings.json`**: Only remove our key; other tools may expect the file to exist\\n- **Reference pattern**: Claude Code's `hooks.go` uses the same `map[string]json.RawMessage` round-trip approach\\n\\n## Files Modified\\n\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/hooks.go` — new functions + integrate into Install/Uninstall\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/hooks_test.go` — ~12 new test cases\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/AGENT.md` — document trusted commands\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n```bash\\nmise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci\\n```\\n\\nThen: `entire enable --force` in test repo → chat in Kiro IDE → hooks should fire without permission prompts.\\n\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":\"tool_use\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":1543,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":108036,\"output_tokens\":79,\"server_tool_use\":{\"web_